.TH "ext4_splice_branch" 9 "ext4_splice_branch" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ext4_splice_branch \- splice the allocated branch onto inode.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ext4_splice_branch
.BI "(handle_t *handle "  ","
.BI "struct ext4_allocation_request *ar "  ","
.BI "Indirect *where "  ","
.BI "int num "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "handle" 12
handle for this transaction
.IP "ar" 12
structure describing the allocation request
.IP "where" 12
location of missing link
.IP "num" 12
number of indirect blocks we are adding
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function fills the missing link and does all housekeeping needed in
inode (->i_blocks, etc.). In case of success we end up with the full
chain to new block and return 0.
